The three ''vaka'' councils of main island [[Rarotonga]] established in 1997 (''Rarotonga Local Government Act 1997''), that were also headed by mayors,&lt;ref&gt;http://www.transparency.org.au/documents/cookislands.pdf&lt;/ref&gt; were abolished in February 2008, despite much controversy&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.cook-islands.gov.ck/view_release.php?release_id=990 RAROTONGA LOCAL GOVERNMENT (REPEAL) BILL TO BE TABLED, Cook Islands Government] and [http://www.ciherald.co.ck/articles/h392b.htm HERALD WEEKLY ISSUE 393 :09 February 2008]&lt;/ref&gt;

;The three ''Vaka'' councils on the main island [[Rarotonga]] were:
